Balance sheet
The teacher should assist the leaner in:-
â€¢ explaining the meaning of a balance sheet.
A balance sheet is a financial statement showing the
assets, capital and liabilities of a business at a
particular time...
explaining the format of a balance sheet the heading
must contain the name of the business, the word
balance sheet and the date of preparation.

Net worth of a business
The teacher should lead the learner in explaining the networth
of a business.
The net worth of a business is the net contribution of the
owner of the business or the net claim by the owner in the
business.
Emphasize that capital represents the networth of the business
i.e.
C = A-L.
